Kanishk Bhaiya, I recently came across your channel. This is perhaps the first time I'm commenting on any yt vdo. Honestly, I couldn't hold myself from thanking you. I am a bona-fide lover of traveling and mountains. The love has been inculcated in me, perhaps by my parents, who took me to a lot of remarkable tours, when I was a kid. I had visited Manebhanjan when I was 7 years old. Now, I'm 17. Back then, I think it wasn't possible to reach Sandakphu via taxi or land rover or any other such conveyance. So, we had trekked through the magical trails amidst the heartbreakingly beautiful mountains. Heartbreaking, since the memory has stayed so intact for a decade....and it slightly hurts when I think about the lucky 7 year old girl hopping through the trails, with a giftedly innocent mind and a heart that was far more capable of love, it kinda makes me feel jealous of her. The memory had been protected and treasured in a deep corner of my heart...ever since its occurrence. Now, when years later, I found your video...I felt the warmth, sunshine and glory of reuniting with an old friend, a place I had shared lovely moments with...the place from where, I had witnessed the majestic Sleeping Buddha for the first time. Thank you, Bhaiya, for this amazing treat to my eyes and heart. It's like, amidst all the mess of competitiveness, pressure and mental stress, which are so highly prevalent in my life right now, you reassured me that, I have places, to seek refuge in...I have places to visit when I grow up, and so...I must go on...â¤
